  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.1.0 (8e100cf 2022-02-17T22:55:47.862863+00:00)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge install dapptools/ds-test\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (amd)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nwhen running forge install on a non-existent github repo, forge will produce a successful install message in the terminal \r\n\r\ne.g.\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n$ forge install dapptools/ds-test\r\nInstalling ds-test in \"/Users/devusr/workspace-contracts/lib/ds-test\", (url: https://github.com/dapptools/ds-test, tag: None)\r\n    Installed ds-test\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis should fail as their is no ds-test repo for dapptools (its located at dapphub/ds-test)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nadditionally, forge install @uniswap/v3-core leaves the install dir at v3-core, can this the scoped package name be the top most directory, i.e. @uniswap? ",
