    "body": "There is no @uniswap/v3-core repository, so it would assume that @uniswap is the owner of the v3-core repository and place it in a submodule named after the repository. I guess we could support an additional name flag or parameter to configure this, but I am not sure how that would affect remappings and the UX of the CLI.\r\n\r\nI think the bug in this issue is caused by us not checking for the exit code of the install commands here: https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/blob/master/cli/src/cmd/install.rs (we just make sure they finish running). Marking this as a good first issue for that reason",
