    "body": "> There is no @uniswap/v3-core repository, so it would assume that @uniswap is the owner of the v3-core repository and place it in a submodule named after the repository. I guess we could support an additional name flag or parameter to configure this, but I am not sure how that would affect remappings and the UX of the CLI.\n> \n> \n> \n> I think the bug in this issue is caused by us not checking for the exit code of the install commands here: https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/blob/master/cli/src/cmd/install.rs (we just make sure they finish running). Marking this as a good first issue for that reason\n\nYes I would not change the existing remapping logic just for this, hence why I am proposing this https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/issues/786\n\nThanks for the quick turnaround",
